Grammy award-winning singer Burna Boy has replaced his crashed Ferrari with a brand new 2022 Lamborghini Urus (Novitec Edition). Burna Boy recently survived an accident with his expensive Ferrari 458 2013. The 30-year-old was involved in an accident in the Lekki area of Lagos on Saturday, February 27, 2022. Burna Boy confirmed he had a “bad accident” with his Ferrari on Instagram but noted he only sustained a minor leg injury. In a new video, the self-acclaimed ‘African Giant’ is seen grinning as he cruises in his latest exotic automobile on the street of Lagos.   Ukraine loses star actor Pasha Lee to Russia invasion     Davido thanks God for successful concert     Korede Bello, Mr Macaroni, Wathoni, others react to BRT…   Burna’s newest ride, a sleek Purple Lamborghini Aventador is worth over N253million. The video had the inscription: “No cap in our rap 7GANG.B7.” Odogwu had indicated interest last year to acquire a Lambo when his colleague, Davido purchased his Lamborghini Aventador. He didn’t hold back his admiration for Davido’s car adding, he may even be considering buying the same for himself, according to his post. He wrote: “That Lambo dey enter my eyes sha”. Although, he didn’t let the post-stay for too long as he deleted it almost immediately.